article.headline: Austin Peay 63, SE Missouri State 56
article.story: CAPE GIRARDEAU, Mo. (AP) -- Zac Schlader scored 14 points and Maurice Hampton had 13 to lead Austin Peay to a 63-56 win over Southeast Missouri State on Saturday night. Roy Booker led Southeast Missouri (6-9, 3-6 Ohio Valley) with 33 points, but the Redhawks shot only 33 percent and had 17 turnovers. Austin Peay (10-6, 5-3) held Southeast Missouri without a field goal for eight minutes to lead 47-31 with 8:39 left. Southeast got within 59-53 with 37 seconds left, but the Governors made their free throws down the stretch. Austin Peay took an early lead, but Southeast Missouri scored 10 straight points late in the first half, and the score was tied 22-22 at halftime. Austin Peay made 24 of 31 free throws.
